==历史==
===史前史===
[[File:Jarlshof_20080821_-_aisled_roundhouse_and_broch.jpg|thumb]]
设得兰群岛这一树木极少的岛上存在着大量的石头建筑，有些可追溯到新石器时代早期。设得兰群岛留存有极为丰富的史前时代建筑遗存，约有超过5000个遗址。<ref>Turner (1998) p. 18</ref>主岛南海岸的[[西湾|西湾]]（West Voe）存有公元前4320-4030年的一座[[贝塚|贝塚]]，这是设得兰群岛上最早的[[中石器时代|中石器时代]]活动遗址。<ref>Melton, Nigel D. "West Voe: A Mesolithic-Neolithic Transition Site in Shetland" in Noble ''et al''（2008）pp. 23, 33</ref><ref>Melton, N. D. & Nicholson R. A.（March 2004）[http://antiquity.ac.uk/Projgall/nicholson/ "The Mesolithic in the Northern Isles: the preliminary evaluation of an oyster midden at West Voe, Sumburgh, Shetland, U.K."] {{Wayback|url=http://antiquity.ac.uk/Projgall/nicholson/ |date=20110628175702 }} ''Antiquity'' '''78''' No 299.</ref>同一位置上人们找到了[[新石器时代|新石器时代]]的一座围墙，检测到其时间年代为公元前3400年。<ref>Fleming (2005) p. 47 quoting Clarke, P.A.（1995）''Observations of Social Change in Prehistoric Orkney and Shetland based on a Study of the Types and Context of Coarse Stone Artefacts''. M. Litt. thesis. University of Glasgow.</ref>“设得兰刀”是用岛上Northmavine的[[霏细岩|霏细岩]]制成的石器。<ref name=Sch10>Schei (2006) p. 10</ref>

Jarlshof的遗迹主要来自[[青铜时代|青铜时代]]，但在其中发现的陶器碎片表明也有新石器时代的活动。<ref>Nicolson (1972) pp. 33–35</ref>这一遗迹中包括铁匠铺、几个集中的圆屋和一座石塔。该遗址证明直到[[维京|维京]]时代，设德兰的人类居所大多采用鞋跟似的石堆修筑而成，这种石头隔间是设德兰独有的。<ref name=jarl>[http://www.shetland-heritage.co.uk/brochures/area_pages/south_mainland/jarlshof_&_scatness.htm " Jarlshof & Scatness"] {{Wayback|url=http://www.shetland-heritage.co.uk/brochures/area_pages/south_mainland/jarlshof_%26_scatness.htm |date=20090710040406 }} shetland-heritage.co.uk. Retrieved 2 August 2008.</ref><ref>Kirk, William "Prehistoric Scotland: The Regional Dimension" in Clapperton (1983) p. 106</ref>在[[韋明特里島|韋明特里島]]有一座典型的隔间建筑。<ref name=Sch10/>

===斯堪的纳维亚人的殖民===
[[File:Flateyjarbok_Haraldr_Halfdan.jpg|thumb]]》描绘的挪威国王[[哈拉尔一世|哈拉尔一世]]，他在875年占领了设得兰]]
斯堪的纳维亚半岛的人口膨胀带来的当地资源和耕地的短缺，导致[[维京人|维京人]]开始出海探险，他们也将注意力从掠夺转向殖民。<ref>Graham-Campbell (1999) p. 38</ref>8到9世纪后期北欧人开始在昔德蘭群島殖民，当地土著人的命运不得而知。今日昔德蘭人血统中斯堪的纳维亚的母系和父系占有几乎相同的比例，这表明北欧殖民者男女共同来到昔德蘭定居。<ref name=Goodacre>Goodacre, S. ''et al''（2005）[http://www.nature.com/hdy/journal/v95/n2/full/6800661a.html#bib14 "Genetic evidence for a family-based Scandinavian settlement of Shetland and Orkney during the Viking periods"] {{Wayback|url=http://www.nature.com/hdy/journal/v95/n2/full/6800661a.html#bib14 |date=20131103184508 }} ''Heredity'' '''95''', pp. 129–135. Nature.com. Retrieved 20 March 2011</ref>

